<plot>Begun with a speech by Vito Russo, Letters enjoins a chorus of speakers to sound off on aids, love and death. Impelled with a variety of formal procedures, this series of mini-portraits are generously furnished with found footage extracts, hand processed dilemmas, home movies, super-8 psycho-drama, pixillated phantasms, intergalactic warfare and a hot kiss in a cool shower.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?333836</url></doc>
